-- в”Ђв”Ђ Mixpanel в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Mixpanel is a product analytics platform that tracks user events, funnels, and retention to help product and growth teams understand behavior in web and mobile apps.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (up to 1M events/month); Growth plan from $0.28 per 1,000 events$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2009, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$500-650 employees (approx.)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California, USA$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Mixpanel Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Mixpanel review: product analytics pricing, event-based plans, key features like funnels and retention, pros, cons, and top alternatives for 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Mixpanel is a product analytics platform used by product, growth, and marketing teams to track user behavior inside web and mobile applications through custom events, funnels, retention curves, and cohort analysis. It was founded in 2009 by Suhail Doshi and Tim Trefren after going through Y Combinator's Summer 2009 batch, and is headquartered in San Francisco, California. The company has raised approximately 277 million dollars in venture funding, including a 200 million dollar Series C in November 2021 led by Bain Capital Tech Opportunities that valued the company at roughly 1.05 billion dollars, giving it unicorn status. Early backers include Andreessen Horowitz, Max Levchin, and Keith Rabois. Suhail Doshi stepped down as CEO in 2018 and was succeeded by Amir Movafaghi, a former Twitter executive; in September 2025 Jen Taylor was named CEO. Mixpanel employs roughly 500 to 650 people across offices on multiple continents.

Architecturally, Mixpanel is an event-based analytics system: instead of tracking pageviews like traditional web analytics tools, it records discrete user actions (events) with associated properties, letting teams build funnels, retention reports, flows, and cohorts without needing SQL. Data can be sent via SDKs (JavaScript, iOS, Android, server-side libraries) or ingested from data warehouses and CDPs like Segment. Core features include Insights and dashboard reporting, Funnels, Retention analysis, Flows (user path analysis), user and event segmentation, cohort building, A/B testing and experimentation tools, session replay, and data pipelines/warehouse connectors such as Snowflake, BigQuery, and Redshift. Mixpanel also offers group analytics, anomaly detection, and a query language and API for custom analysis.

Pricing is freemium and, as of February 2026, event-based rather than tracked-user based. The Free plan covers up to 1 million events per month with unlimited seats, five saved reports, and 10,000 session replays per month. The Growth plan starts billing at 0.28 dollars per 1,000 events once usage exceeds the free 1 million, with unlimited seats and reports and 20,000 free session replays; typical costs run roughly 1,120 dollars per month at 5 million events and about 2,520 dollars per month at 10 million events. Enterprise pricing is custom and adds unlimited events, data governance controls, dedicated support, and custom SLAs; legacy MTU-based Enterprise plans are still available starting around 20,000 dollars per year for organizations that prefer that pricing model.

Mixpanel's target audience is product managers, growth teams, and engineers at SaaS, mobile app, and consumer companies who need granular behavioral analytics beyond what Google Analytics offers. Its main competitors include Amplitude, Google Analytics 4, Heap, PostHog, and open-source or self-hosted alternatives such as OpenPanel. Mixpanel differentiates itself with a polished no-code interface for funnels and retention, strong mobile app analytics support, and a shift to consumption-based, event-volume pricing intended to be more predictable than the older MTU model.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '9163dedf-1317-4248-a79a-e9fd4b8cf999';

