-- в”Ђв”Ђ Mixxx в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Mixxx is a free, open-source DJ mixing application for Windows, macOS, and Linux that lets DJs beatmix, loop, and scratch digital music using a virtual interface or hardware controllers.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Open Source$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2002, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE(NULL, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Mixxx Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Mixxx review: free open-source DJ software features, controller support, vinyl control (DVS), pricing (free), and alternatives compared for 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Mixxx is a free, open-source DJ mixing application available for Windows, macOS, and Linux that lets DJs mix, beatmatch, loop, and scratch digital audio files using either an on-screen virtual deck interface or external MIDI/HID DJ controllers. The project originated in 2002 as part of a PhD thesis on new interfaces for DJing by Tue Haste Andersen, who released it as open source in response to a lack of DJ software for Linux and dissatisfaction with proprietary Windows and Mac DJ tools of the era. In 2006 a new team led by Adam Davison and Albert Santoni took over development and reorganized the project for sustainable growth; RJ Ryan became lead developer in 2011. Unlike most DJ software, Mixxx is not backed by a company; it has no headquarters, no employees, and no venture funding. Development and maintenance are entirely community-driven, carried out by volunteer programmers and DJs, and sustained by user donations. As of Mixxx 2.0, more than 100 developers and artists have contributed to the codebase, and the software is downloaded more than 1 million times a year, making it one of the most widely used free DJ applications.

Technically, Mixxx is built in C++ using the Qt framework and is licensed under the GNU General Public License. It supports lossless audio formats (FLAC, WAV, AIFF) as well as lossy formats (MP3, M4A/AAC, Ogg Vorbis, Opus). Core features include automatic BPM detection and beat sync, multiple virtual decks, hot cues, loops, effects racks, a built-in music library manager with crate and playlist support, live broadcasting via Shoutcast/Icecast, and full MIDI/HID controller mapping support, including the ability to write custom controller mappings in JavaScript, a capability that is uncommon among DJ software. Mixxx also supports vinyl control (DVS, Digital Vinyl System), letting DJs control digital tracks using timecoded vinyl or CDs (such as Serato-compatible timecode) through a standard multi-channel audio interface, making it one of the only free timecode vinyl control solutions available on Windows, macOS, and Linux.

Because Mixxx is entirely free and open source, there is no pricing model, no tiers, and no paid upgrade path; all features are available to everyone under the same GPL license. Its target audience includes bedroom and hobbyist DJs, Linux users underserved by commercial DJ software, budget-conscious mobile and wedding DJs, and DJs who want a fully scriptable, hackable mixing platform. Its main competitors are commercial DJ applications such as Serato DJ Pro, rekordbox (Pioneer DJ), VirtualDJ, and Traktor Pro, all of which require paid licenses or controller bundles. Mixxx differentiates itself as one of the only mainstream DJ applications that is both free and open source, cross-platform with native Linux support, and scriptable via JavaScript for custom hardware integrations, appealing to users who value transparency, community governance, and zero cost over the polish and label partnerships of commercial rivals.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '909db6fb-d649-46c3-9386-4c38e0917e64';

